cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the issue of detecting malicious websites and proposes a new certificate transparency scheme with enhanced security features. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it addresses the issue of online security and privacy. The use of Merkle hash trees suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SE (Software Engineering) as these fields deal with efficient data structures and algorithms. Finally, the use of dynamic bilinear-map accumulators suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as this field deals with distributed systems and algorithms.
